a.xlink:title: Program entry: run all kernel tests and print "ok test_kernels" on success.
Row-wise GEMV kernel: each thread computes one output row.
Install the best available CPU kernels for this process.
Test: GEMV without bias, row-major, blk_k=0.
Test: GEMV with bias epilogue, row-major, blk_k=0.
Generic C GEMV: y = W * x (+bias), optional blocked-K traversal.
Fill a small, deterministic row-major matrix W[r,c] = (r+1)*0.1 + (c+1)*0.01.
Fill a small, deterministic vector x[i] = 0.05 * (i+1).
Compute reference row-major GEMV y = W*x (no bias).
Compare two float vectors with absolute tolerance.
